{{Refimprove|date=October 2013}} {{Infobox book | name = I, Tina | title_orig = | translator = | image = File:I, Tina.jpg | caption = Cover of the first edition | author = [[Tina Turner]] | illustrator = | cover_artist = | country = United States | language = English | series = | subject = | publisher = [[William Morrow and Company]] | pub_date = September 1st, 1986 | english_pub_date = | media_type = Print (Paperback) | pages = 207 | isbn = | oclc = | dewey = | congress = | preceded_by = | followed_by = }}
'''''I, Tina''''' is a 1986 autobiography by [[Rock music|rock singer]] [[Tina Turner]], co-written by [[MTV]] news correspondent and music critic [[Kurt Loder]].<ref name=LATimes>{{cite news|url=http://articles.latimes.com/1993-05-16/entertainment/ca-35747_1_tina-turner/3 |title=SUMMER SNEAKS : Tina Turner's Story Through a Disney Prism : The singer's film biography, 'What's Love Got to Do With It,' focuses on her turbulent relationship with her mentor and ex-husband Ike Turner as well as her triumphant comeback - Los Angeles Times |publisher=Articles.latimes.com/ |date=1993-05-16 |accessdate=2013-10-06 |first=Michael |last=Walker}}</ref> It described Turner's story from a girl born and raised in [[Nutbush, Tennessee]] to her initial rise to fame under the leadership of famed [[blues]] musician [[Ike Turner]] and her abusive relationship with the [[St. Louis, Missouri|St. Louis]] [[guitarist]] that ended in 1976 to her 1980s comeback. The book became a worldwide best-seller when it was released and led to the film adaptation, ''[[What's Love Got to Do with It (film)|What's Love Got to Do with It]]'', in 1993 starring [[Angela Bassett]] as Turner.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oprah.com/omagazine/Oprahs-Interview-with-Tina-Turner |title=Oprah's Interview with Tina Turner |publisher=Oprah.com |date= |accessdate=2013-10-05}}</ref><ref name=LATimes/>
